  "name": "Wind Beneath Your Wings",
  "type": "spell",
  "effects": [],
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Access </strong>pegasus or griffon</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Cast </strong>[one-action] verbal</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Duration </strong>1 round</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"> </p>\n<hr />\n<p> </p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">You suddenly surge forward, borne on a gust of wind that propels you at incredible speeds. Your fly Speed increases by 10 feet, gaining a fly Speed if you did not have one, and gain a +4 status bonus to AC against reactions prompted by moving before the start of your next turn.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"> </p>\n<hr />\n<p> </p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Heightened </strong>(+1) Increase your bonus to fly Speed by 5 feet.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Heightened </strong>(+1) Increase the duration of the spell by 1 minute.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Heightened </strong>(+1) Increase the range of the spell to 60 feet and you may target a creature to gain this benefit in addition to yourself.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Heightened</strong> (+1) If you end your movement in the air and can't otherwise fly, rather than falling, you may attempt to Arrest a Fall despite the failing magic.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"> </p>"
